Guy Davenport (1927-2005) was a writer and painter born in Anderson, South Carolina. He attended Duke, Oxford University as a Rhodes scholar, and Harvard (PhD). He taught at Harvard, Haverford, and the University of Kentucky. His awards included the Morton Dawen Zabel Award for Fiction by the American Academy &amp; Institute of Arts and Letters, and a MacArthur Fellowship.


